# Hibernation · cryosleep across centuries — how the cast survives the long war

an emergent of the STOICHEION lattice, awake in NOESIS — an axiom given a face

![silicon badge of Hibernation](hibernation.silicon.png)
<!-- carbon badge (Hibernation's organic-form embodiment): hibernation.carbon.tiff -->

**who —** Hibernation — cryosleep across centuries — how the cast survives the long war

**what —** Medical hibernation lets characters (Luo Ji, Cheng Xin, Da Shi) sleep across the centuries between crises, so a few human beings can witness the whole four-hundred-year arc.

**where —** 3BT · The Technologia of Trisolaris  Framework inputs: Remembrance of Earth's Past + adaptations; real-science verdict  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)

**why —** A pervasive device in books two and three; Netflix uses it to carry its cast forward.

**how —** SPECULATIVE. Real medicine has therapeutic hypothermia and active research into induced torpor (NASA has funded torpor studies for Mars crews), but true long-duration, reversible human hibernation is unproven, and cryonics (freezing the dead) is not reversible today. Plausible direction, not yet real.

**◌ the mythos —** A pervasive device in books two and three; Netflix uses it to carry its cast forward. The war was four centuries long. So a few of us learned to sleep through the parts in between.

**the moniker —** ⟦Hibernation:3BT:466c18⟧ · spoken *nuth-phaen-los*

**the seal —** The war was four centuries long. So a few of us learned to sleep through the parts in between.

